St.Ack

&gt; I was able to finish the experimentation of Heritrix on windows and found 
&gt; out that it has to do with the DNS Java components. I tried on windows XP, 
&gt; windows 2003 server enterprise edition set up as IIS and DNS servers on the 
&gt; network. Debugging the puppy shows that the calls are not making it through 
&gt; the system to the DNS Cache on the windows boxes, while on Red Hat 9.0 which 
&gt; I happily had a copy of, the system was up and running in a couple of hours 
&gt; collecting arc files.
&gt;
&gt; Essentially then if I can get DNS Java working on the windows box (which has 
&gt; been the stumbling point at this time) then I should be able to do a good 
&gt; crawl using Heritrix. No worries there, it is going to be an interesting 
&gt; time if I decide to stay with Linux. Which I probably well because I am time 
&gt; constrained hugely lately.
